This article is a press gaggle from February 17, 2009, with Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. He discusses various topics such as the possibility of giving GM another $4 billion, the foreclosure plan, the restructuring of the auto industry, the economic stimulus package, the appointment of key positions in the administration, the fiscal responsibility summit, and foreign policy issues. He also mentions that President Obama will be signing a bill for the largest economic recovery package in the country's history.